# Tech Lead Audit — Docs Selection

Before auditing, read:

- `/docs/decision-log.md` (always)
- `.cursor/rules/07-tech-lead-audit-policy.mdc` and relevant `audit/*` checklists

## By audited area

Combine paths from category rules; dedupe.

| Audit focus | Also read |
|-------------|-----------|
| Full stack / release readiness | `overview.md`, `business-process-map.md`, `boundaries-workflow.md`, `domain-lifecycle.md`, `database-schema.md`, `modules-reliability.md`, `security-observability-testing.md`, `contracts.md`, `implementation-plan-v1.md` |
| Invoice workflow | `80-invoice-workflow.mdc` list + `boundaries-workflow.md`, `domain-lifecycle.md`, `business-process-map.md` |
| DB / migrations / repos | `10-db-persistence.mdc` list + `database-schema.md` |
| Lifecycle / statuses | `20-lifecycle-statuses.mdc` list + `domain-lifecycle.md` |
| API / DTO / controllers | `30-dto-api-controllers.mdc` list + `contracts.md` |
| Validation / mapping | `40-validation-mapping.mdc` list |
| Bitrix24 | `50-bitrix24.mdc` list |
| Fakturownia | `60-fakturownia.mdc` list |
| Tests only | `70-testing.mdc` list + `security-observability-testing.md` |

Do not use legacy doc paths listed as forbidden in `01-core-implementation-agent.mdc`.

If docs conflict with code: report as **Medium** (docs/rules contradiction); do not improvise fixes during audit unless asked.
